    <description>
A production-ready MQTT client library for .NET nanoFramework that simplifies connecting embedded devices (ESP32) to the Azure Event Grid Namespace MQTT broker.

Core features:
- Simple API: Connect(), Publish(), Subscribe(), Disconnect()
- X.509 certificate authentication with PEM string input
- MQTT v5.0 and v3.1.1 protocol support
- Automatic reconnection with configurable exponential backoff
- Last Will and Testament (LWT) for device presence
- JSON publish helper with automatic serialization
- Subscription persistence across reconnections

Extensible modules:
- Device Twin: desired/reported state sync over MQTT
- Health Reporting: periodic heartbeat with uptime, memory, counters
- Certificate Rotation: expiry monitoring, OTA cert update, runtime swap
- Custom Message Handlers: plug-in architecture via IMqttMessageHandler

Extensibility:
- IEventGridMqttClient interface for dependency injection and testing
- ILogger interface for pluggable logging (DebugLogger, NullLogger included)
- IMqttMessageHandler for custom message processing modules
    </description>
    <tags>nanoFramework C# csharp netnf iot mqtt azure eventgrid esp32 embedded certificate x509 reconnect tls</tags>
